new_study <- new_study |>
mutate(depr_cat = if_else(depr_total < 10, "Normal",
if_else(depr_total >= 10 & depr_total < 14, "Mild",
if_else(depr_total >= 14 & depr_total < 21, "Moderate",
if_else(depr_total >= 21 & depr_total < 28, "Severe","Extremely Severe")))))

#Transfer depression category as a factor

new_study <- mutate(new_study, depr_cat = as.factor(depr_cat))

#Relevel depression category

new_study <- mutate(new_study, depr_cat = fct_relevel(depr_cat,"Normal", "Mild", "Moderate", "Severe","Extremely Severe"))

#Centering Predictors

new_study <- 
  new_study |>
  mutate(familysize.cent = (familysize - mean(familysize)))

#Mean centering gender

  new_study |>
  mutate (gender.cent = ifelse(gender == 1, .5, -.5), 
          gender.cent = as.factor (gender.cent),
          gender.cent = fct_recode(gender.cent, "Male" = "0.5", "Female" = "-0.5"))

#Bootstrapping

#Load relevant packages
library (caret)
## Warning: package 'caret' was built under R version 4.3.2
## Loading required package: lattice
## 
## Attaching package: 'caret'
## The following object is masked from 'package:purrr':
## 
##     lift
library (rsample)
## Warning: package 'rsample' was built under R version 4.3.2
#Ensure getting same results during randomization for bootstrapping
set.seed (100)
boots <- bootstraps(data=new_study , times = 1000, apparent = TRUE)

#Construct helper function
fit_lm_boot <- function(split){lm(depr_total ~ familysize.cent + gender.cent, data = analysis(split))}

#Fitting linear model to bootstrap resamples
boot_models <- boots |> 
  mutate(model = map (splits, fit_lm_boot), 
      coef_info = map(model, tidy))
      
boot_coefs <- boot_models |> 
  unnest (coef_info)

#Derive confidence interval
percentile_intervals <- int_pctl (boot_models, coef_info)

percentile_intervals
